        "## Debugging\n",
        "\n",
        "Note that most list methods modify the argument and return `None`.\n",
        "This is the opposite of the string methods, which return a new string and leave the original alone.\n",
        "\n",
        "If you are used to writing string code like this:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "88872f14",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "88872f14"
